The paper deals with image registration and alignment, which is a common problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of the tangent distance method, which is a machine learning algorithm and can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of multiscale pyramids and filtering techniques, which are commonly used in image processing and can be categorized under information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
